{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78d48216-82d8-4929-9eca-f1a02121d686","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's a summary:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ **`netcoreapp3.1`** — no longer supported (EOL)\n- ❌ **`net5.0`** — no longer supported (EOL)\n- ✅ **`net462`** — still supported\n\nYou'll need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to use currently supported runtimes (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n\n**Package changes in MSTest v3:**\n- The separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are consolidated into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package, simplifying the reference.\n\n**Action needed:** Update your target frameworks to supported versions before (or as part of) upgrading to MSTest v3.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"44419df8-7fb7-4d3e-a7a1-c6c211be31de","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project that multi-targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks. Specifically, MSTest v3 requires at minimum:\n   - .NET 6.0+ (for .NET Core/5+)\n   - .NET Framework 4.6.2 is still supported, but let me verify\n\nActually, let me think more carefully about MSTest v3 compatibility:\n\n\n- MSTest v3 dropped support for `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` since both are out of support, so the user will run into compatibility issues with those two target frameworks. The `net462` target should continue to work fine.\n- MSTest v3 also consolidates the separate packages into a single `MSTest` package instead of requiring multiple packages.","outputTokens":562,"requestId":"7C12:1E67:4F17BB:5DCC87:69F95ADD"},"id":"64e98164-8140-44f2-b54a-aded7d89dcc7","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:50:18.181Z","parentId":"7ff8a04a-b571-4bc4-b0fb-4202b0322195"}
